sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Update a record in Microsoft Dynamics CRM.

Inputs:

  • Entity - Entity for which you wish to update a record.
  • Record ID - ID of the record which you wish to update.
  • Fields - Add the fields and values with which you wish to update the record.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • Provided Record ID is invalid or not provided.
  • Provided Entity is invalid.
  • Provided value for Fields input is invalid.
  • Invalid username or password/token or the token has expired.
  • The credentials associated with the Microsoft Dynamics CRM Spoke connection does not have enough permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding Microsoft Dynamics CRM connection and credential must be created and associated with the Microsoft Dynamics CRM Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
